<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">Words Starting With MIS-</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">Word of the Day · Dictionary · English Solver</p>

<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The MIS- prefix means "wrongly" or "badly" and turns any verb into its erroneous counterpart. With over 500 valid MIS- words in SOWPODS, this prefix gives you a scoring edge because M is worth 3 points — higher than most prefix-starting tiles. MISJUDGE, MISQUOTE, and MISPLACE all deliver serious points.</p>

<p>MIS- is especially powerful for extensions: if JUDGE, QUOTE, or PLACE appear on the board, you can prepend MIS for an instant high-scoring play.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why MIS- Matters in Scrabble</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">M(3)+I(1)+S(1) base</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">500+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid MIS- words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3–15</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter length range</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>The M tile's 3-point value makes MIS- more valuable per letter than DIS- or UN-. With only 2 M tiles in the bag, landing one early and pairing it with the common I and S tiles sets up powerful scoring opportunities.</p>

